			<div class="col-sm-12 discl_rules"><br>
				<b>1. ELIGIBILITY</b>:
				The {!! trans('landing.jeep') !!} Find Your Freedom Contest (“Contest”) is open to legal residents of the continental United States (including the District of Columbia) and Hawaii who are 18 years of age or older and have reached the age of majority in their state as of date of entry and who pre-order a 2019 {!! trans('landing.jeep') !!} Gladiator from an authorized {!! trans('landing.jeep') !!} dealer on April 3 - April 4, 2019 during the official vehicle pre-sale.  Contest is void in Arizona, Colorado, Maryland, Nebraska, Vermont, North Dakota and Puerto Rico and wherever prohibited by law, or where the registration or filing requirements of any state or local jurisdiction have not been complied with. Employees of FCA US LLC ("Sponsor"), Relevent and The Promotion Pipeline, Inc. (herein after collectively “Administrators”), and their respective affiliates, subsidiaries, advertising, production and promotion agencies, and the immediate families and members of the same household of each are not eligible. All federal, state, local and municipal laws and regulations apply. By participating in this Contest, an entrant agrees to be bound by these Official Rules and that the decisions of Sponsor shall be final and binding in all matters pertaining to the Contest, including, but not limited to, interpretation and application of these Official Rules. 
				<hr> 
			</div>
			
			<div class="col-sm-12 discl_rules">
				<b>2. HOW TO ENTER</b>:
				Contest begins at 9:00:00 am Eastern Time (“ET”) on April 3, 2019 and ends at 11:59:59 pm ET on April 30, 2019 (“Promotion Period”). Visit www.JeepFindYourFreedom.com to complete the entry form and upload a video conveying your personal Gladiator story explaining how you would spend a year off from work.  Entrants agree to be bound by and acknowledge compliance with these official rules including eligibility requirements.  The entrant is deemed to be the person whose name is on the deposit payment.  If the deposit payment is made by a business the entrant is must be an authorized representative of the business.  Limit one (1) entry per person, regardless of e-mail address. A selected winner may be asked to provide Sponsor with proof that the selected winner is the person who made the deposit or is an authorized representative of the business associated with the winning entry.  If a dispute cannot be resolved, the entry will be deemed ineligible.  Use of automated devices not valid for entry. Entries become the exclusive property of the Sponsor and will not be returned.<hr>
			</div>
			
			<div class="col-sm-12 discl_rules">
				<b>3. SUBMISSION REQUIREMENTS</b>:
				Submission must be an original :60 to :75 video taken by the entrant explaining how you would spend a year off from work (“Submission”).  No stock videos can be used.  Any entry which in the sole opinion of Sponsor is deemed to be inappropriate for publication will be deemed ineligible.  Once a Submission is posted it cannot be changed, altered or modified.  Submission (a) must be the original and sole creation of, and all right, title and interest including but not limited to the copyright in the video must be owned solely by the entrant; (b) may not contain any nudity or any inappropriate images as solely determined by the Sponsor; (c) may not have been submitted in any other competition; (d) may not have been published, including postings on the World Wide Web, prior to the Contest Submission other than via the entrant’s social media channels; (e) may not infringe upon any third party's rights, including but not limited to copyright, patent or trademarks/tradenames/logos (other than Sponsor’s logos), or rights of privacy or publicity, or contain material that is or may be considered defamatory, slanderous or libelous, or portray in a false light;  (f) may not violate any law, rule or regulation; (g)must not display any reckless driving or depict Sponsor’s products being used in a manner that is inconsistent with the Owner’s Manual or New Vehicle Limited Warranty, or encourages others to use Sponsor’s products in a manner that is inconsistent with the Owner’s Manual or New Vehicle Limited Warranty; (h) must not describe or depict Sponsor’s products being used in an inappropriate, unsafe, irresponsible or unlawful manner, or encourage others to use Sponsors’ products in an inappropriate, unsafe, irresponsible or unlawful manner; (i) must not include any activity that damages the environment; and (j) must not feature a steering wheel or otherwise directly or indirectly imply that the photo was taken while driving or in a moving vehicle.</br></br>Each entrant warrants and represents that his/her video complies with all of those conditions. If individuals other than the entrant appear in the Submission those individuals must give their express consent to appear in the Submission.  Sponsor may ask entrant to provide written permission from such individuals that is satisfactory to Sponsor.   Other individuals featured in a Submission are not deemed to be the Contest entrant.  Non-complying Submissions will be subject to disqualification.   By entering, each entrant grants permission for the use of the Submission, and his/her name, to be used across all Sponsor-operated digital properties, including without limitation websites and social channels, in connection with this Contest, and the advertising, promotion, and publicity of the Contest, and otherwise, as stated in these Official Rules (as solely determined by Sponsor).
				<hr>
			</div>
			
			
			<div class="col-sm-12 discl_rules">
				<b>4. JUDGING</b>:
				At the conclusion of the Promotion Period all eligible entries submitted into the Contest will be judged by a panel composed of employees of Sponsor and an independent judge whose decisions are final and binding on all judging matters.   Submissions will be judged 70% on inspirational message relating to that of a gladiator storyline, 30% on consistency with {!! trans('landing.jeep') !!} brand image.  In the event of a tie, the entry with the highest score in “inspirational message relating to that of a gladiator storyline” will be deemed the winner.
				<hr>
			</div>
			
